section.section:
Of the 15 members of the Commission:
one shall be the President of the Maryland Chiefs of Police Association;
one shall be the President of the Maryland Sheriffs Association;
one shall be the President of the Maryland Law Enforcement Officers, Inc.;
one shall be the Attorney General of the State;
one shall be the Secretary of State Police;
one shall be the Police Commissioner of Baltimore City;
one shall be the Chancellor of the University System of Maryland;
one shall be the agent in charge of the Baltimore office of the FBI;
one shall be the President of the Eastern Shore Police Association;
one shall represent the Maryland State Lodge of Fraternal Order of Police;
one shall be the Secretary of Public Safety and Correctional Services;
one shall be the Chairman of the Maryland Municipal League Police Executive Association; and
three shall be police officials of the State appointed under subsection (b) of this section.
